      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 2,
      "creation_date" : 1382222041,
      "post_id" : 2293195,
      "comment_id" : 28876933,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "First, it&#39;s not a conversion: it&#39;s the removal of non-printable bytes. Second, it assumes that the underlying OS&#39; default encoding is really based on ASCII for printable characters (won&#39;t work on IBM Mainframes using EBCDIC, for instance)."
    } ],
